<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-23T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-23T19:00:00-05:00" n="739" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d739">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/7794</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Rumania</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_VCJ1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Vopicka</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-23T19:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">January 23, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>130. Referring to Department’s 91, November 28,<note n="2" xml:id="d739fn2">
                                    <ref target="frus1917Supp02v01#pg_325">
                                        <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>
                                    </ref>
                                </note> please reiterate assurances conveyed by the President to the
                                King of Roumania. Full text of President’s address to Congress was
                                repeated to you by radio from Saloniki. This Government has no
                                knowledge of any understanding between Roumania and her other allies
                                in regard to peace terms,<note n="3" xml:id="d739fn3">Referring to
                                    the Minister’s telegram No. 161, Nov. 17, 1917, <ref target="frus1917Supp02v01#pg_309">
                                        <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, p. 309</ref>.</note> but is,
                                however, committed to safeguard the integrity and freedom of smaller
                                nations.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>